<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="844" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d844">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Tower</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-12-31"><hi rend="italic">December 31,
                                    1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 269.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: For your information I have to inclose
                            herewith copies of correspondence<note n="a" xml:id="d844fna">Printed,
                                ante.</note> with the Russian ambassador at this capital in
                            reference to the reported acts of the United States consul at Niuchwang;
                            also copy of the Department’s instruction to Mr. Miller in the
                            matter.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>